    "created_at": "2017-09-07T16:07:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-09-07T16:07:13Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for writing the clarifications.  Would it be possible to squeeze in a mention that the status returned is UNAVAILABLE for transient failures with fail-fast (like #12390 is attempting to do).\r\n\r\nAlso, I'd change \"MUST be cautious\" into \"should be cautious\".  \"Being cautious\" is subjective and not specific, so it's pretty hard to say if a gRPC implementation is cautious.  If we can define a specific set of requirements here, using \"MUST\" would be appropriate.  E.g. \"gRPC implementations MUST NOT make more than three attempts that could reach the [or 'a single'?] remote server\"."
  },
