    "created_at": "2017-09-07T18:05:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-09-07T18:05:01Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> How isn't it related? This is the only place that discusses \"fail fast\", and this status code is returned as a result of a fail fast RPC encountering a transient failure.\r\n\r\nThis does not _define_ fail fast. This document only discussed it to contrast. Yes, this is the only place that mentions the term \"fail fast\", but that's in part because the term _does not exist_ in gRPC. We only have \"wait for ready\". The \"default behavior\" (sometimes called \"fail fast\") should be defined elsewhere."
  },
