    "created_at": "2017-09-07T21:19:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-09-07T21:19:29Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> The \"default behavior\" (sometimes called \"fail fast\") should be defined elsewhere.\r\n\r\nThis document _does_ define the default behavior:\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n> By default, gRPC implementations SHOULD fail such RPCs immediately.\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n> by default, gRPC implementations SHOULD immediately return the error to the client application\r\n\r\nUntil a separate document exists that more thoroughly defines the default behavior, I think it's perfectly reasonable to add one extra detail to the behavior that is described here."
  },
